subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
This species is distinguished from all other species in the genus 

Luispenaia

by the following combination of characters: Body dorsally reddish brown, shiny on legs and elytra; head pronotum and scutellum black or dark brown (
Fig. 18
). Clypeus distal and laterally rounded, reflexed upturned; lateral margin between clypeal base and ocular canthus projected externally as a lobule moderately projecting (
Fig. 10
). Antennae with 9 antennomeres; antennal club with 6 antennomeres (
Fig. 17
). Pronotum approximately subtrapezoidal, broadest in middle, laterally arcuate; surface with longitudinal midline impunctate (
Fig. 10
).
